Women massively outnumber men? UN population projections show no such thing             AFP  17th Jun 2019 11:50:51 GMT +0300 AFP  17th Jun 2019 11:50:51 GMT +0300 AFP   A screenshot of shared articles trashed as verified as fake news by AFP Fact Check desk. [AFP]  A screenshot of shared articles trashed as verified as fake news by AFP Fact Check desk. [AFP] A screenshot of shared articles trashed as verified as fake news by AFP Fact Check desk. [AFP] A screenshot of shared articles trashed as verified as fake news by AFP Fact Check desk. A newspaper article shared thousands of times in Nigeria claims that there are only 2.2 billion men in a world that has 5.6 billion women, quoting a “1st Quarter Demography Report 2019” by the United Nations. This is false; the UN Population Division confirmed the latest world population projection to AFP as 3.82 billion females and 3.89 billion males. The report by Nigerian newspaper Daily Independent, which brands itself as “the most read newspaper among business and political elites”, claims that there are now 7.8 billion people in the world.    here here here here  here  here    Register to advertise your products & services on our classifieds website Digger.co.ke and enjoy one month subscription free of charge and 3 free ads on the Standard newspaper. Register to advertise your products & services on our classifieds website Digger.co.ke and enjoy one month subscription free of charge and 3 free ads on the Standard newspaper. Digger.co.ke Related Topics UNFPA UN Population Fake News Men Women